She was speaking in an exclusive interview with the South African Broadcasting Corporation News as millions of workers celebrate May Day on Sunday. Cosatu is holding its main Workersâ€™ Day celebrations at the Royal Bafokeng stadium in Rustenburg in the North West where the African National Congress (ANC) President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to deliver the main address. Losi says they believe government has abandoned South African workers. Meanwhile the Congress of the People has called on workers to unite in the fight for their rights in the workplace. The party has accused Cosatu of abandoning workers, saying it has been captured by the ANC.

